Anh - Anh
louis
['lu:i]
(also louis d'or-'dɔ:)
■ noun (plural same 'lu:ɪz)
1》 a French gold coin issued between 1640 and 1793.
2》 another term for napoleon (in sense 1).
Origin
from Louis, the name of many kings of France.
